snippet: Russia announced that a flotilla of navy vessels had sailed to the Mediterranean Sea and some would dock in the Syrian port of Tartus.
abstract: Russia announces that it has dispatched a flotilla of 11 warships to the eastern Mediterranean, some of which will dock in Syria; announcement punctuates Russia’s effort to position itself as an increasingly decisive broker in resolving the antigovernment uprising in Syria, its closest partner in the Middle East.

byline.original: By ANDREW E. KRAMER and RICK GLADSTONE
byline.contributor: Andrew E. Kramer reported from Moscow, and Rick Gladstone from New York. Reporting was contributed by Thomas Erdbrink from Tehran, Duraid Adnan from Baghdad, Peter E. Baker from Washington and Dalal Mawad from Beirut.

lead_paragraph: Russia announced that a flotilla of navy vessels had sailed to the Mediterranean Sea and some would dock in the Syrian port of Tartus.
